ciscoSwitchQosMIB.description: This MIB module extends the CISCO-CLASS-BASED-QOS-MIB by defining configuration and statistics information specific to the quality of service (QoS) features of Layer2/3 switch functionality implemented in Cisco devices. It is applicable to a device which is fully within a single QoS domain, although one or more boundaries with other QoS domains can be immediately adjacent to this device. Configuration information available through this MIB includes: + Mappings between CoS, IP Precedence, MPLS-EXP value to DSCP value and vice versa for classification purpose. + Device level QoS configuration for DSCP rewrite, policing of ACL-redirected traffic, QoS port-queueing mode, statistics collection for policy that sets a trust state. + CoS, MPLS-EXP and DSCP mutation map name and mappings. These mutations can be configured so that they change the content of packets which cross QoS boundaries, either as they enter or leave this device. + Interface QoS configuration such as default CoS value, trust state, packet assignment to queue and threshold based on CoS or DSCP value, drop algorithm and corresponding parameters, queue scheduling parameter such as WRR (Weighted Round Robin) weights, queue size allocation weight. Statistics available through this MIB includes: + Per module Multi-Layer Switching QoS statistics. + Per interface QoS queueing statistics. The following terms are used throughout this MIB: DSCP (Differentiated Services Code Point) is the six most significant bits of the ToS field in a IP packet header. DSCP Mutation: when a packet is being forwarded across an IP network, the previous hop(s) and the following hop(s) of a device may reside in a different QoS domain. A QoS domain refers to the set of QoS rules and conventions adopted by an administrative entity. For instance, a set of DSCP values may have a different meaning in different domains. DSCP mutation allows a DSCP set to be mutated or transformed in order to maintain semantic compatibility between adjacent domains. The mutation is done via mapping tables which maps the old DSCP value from one domain to a new DSCP value in the other domain. DSCP Mutation is applied to egress traffic. IP precedence is the three most significant bits of the ToS field in a IP packet header. CoS (Class of Service) is the three bits in the layer 2 header that indicates user priority value assigned to this packet. Trust state is a parameter configured at an interface to specify which QoS markings in packets arriving at that interface are acceptable as-is, rather than needing to be ignored/overwritten due to an 'untrusted' source or previous hop. BPDU (Bridge Protocol Data Unit) is used by bridges in a network to exchange information regarding their status. The Spanning Tree Protocol uses the BPDU information to elect the root switch and root port for the switched network. MPLS-EXP: MPLS experimental field in MPLS label. MTU: Maximum Transmission Unit.

QosStatsType.description: An integer indicating a specific statistics. ucastSentPkts(1): Unicast packets sent ucastSentBytes(2): Unicast bytes sent mcastSentPkts(3): Multicast packets sent mcastSentBytes(4): Multicast bytes sent ucastDroppedPkts(5): Unicast packets dropped ucastDroppedBytes(6): Unicast bytes dropped mcastDroppedPkts(7): Multicast packets dropped mcastDroppedBytes(8): Multicast bytes dropped sentPkts(9): Packets sent receivedPkts(10): Packets received droppedIngressPkts(11): Packets discarded on ingress ucastSentXbarPkts(12): Unicast packets sent to the cross-bar ucastRecvXbarPkts(13): Unicast packets received from the cross-bar mcastSentXbarPkts(14): Multicast packets sent to the cross-bar mcastRecvXbarPkts(15): Multicast packets received from the cross-bar ucastSentOobfcPkts(16): Unicast packets sent on OOBFC ucastSentOobfcBytes(17): Unicast bytes sent on OOBFC ucastDroppedOobfcPkts(18): Unicast packets dropped on OOBFC ucastDroppedOobfcBytes(19): Unicast bytes dropped on OOBFC ucastWatchdogDroppedPkts(20): Unicast packets dropped after watchdog triggered

csqDscpRewriteEnable.name: csqDscpRewriteEnable
csqDscpRewriteEnable.description: This object specifies whether DSCP rewrite is enabled at a device-level of granularity, i.e., 'true' = enabled and 'false' = disabled. If no other objects specify whether DSCP rewrite is enabled at any different level of granularity, then this object's value is not subject to any modifiers. However, some devices might support other object(s) which specify whether DSCP rewrite is enabled at different level(s) of granularity. For such devices, the value of this object takes precedence over the values of such other object(s) when the value of this object is 'false'; in contrast, when the value of this object is 'true', the values of such other objects take precedence over the value of this object. if 'true', all outgoing packets will have their DSCP value rewritten based on the result of classification, policing or DSCP mutation configured in the device. if 'false', all outgoing packets will have their DSCP values unchanged from they arrived.

csqPoliceRedirectedTrafficEnable.name: csqPoliceRedirectedTrafficEnable
csqPoliceRedirectedTrafficEnable.description: This object specifies whether ACL-redirected traffic policing is enabled at a device-level of granularity, i.e., 'true' = enabled and 'false' = disabled. If no other objects specify whether ACL-redirected traffic is enabled at any different level of granularity, then this object's value is not subject to any modifiers. However, some devices might support other object(s) which specify whether ACL-redirected traffic policing is enabled at different level(s) of granularity. For such devices, the value of this object takes precedence over the values of such other object(s) when the value of this object is 'false'; in contrast, when the value of this object is 'true', the values of such other objects take precedence over the value of this object. if 'true', ACL-redirected traffic is subject to policing. if 'false', ACL-redirected traffic is not policed.

csqPortQueueingModeEnable.name: csqPortQueueingModeEnable
csqPortQueueingModeEnable.description: This object specifies whether port-queueing mode is enabled at a device-level of granularity, i.e., 'true' = enabled and 'false' = disabled. If no other objects specify whether port-queueing mode is enabled at any different level of granularity, then this object's value is not subject to any modifiers. However, some devices might support other object(s) which specify whether port-queueing mode is enabled at different level(s) of granularity. For such devices, the value of this object takes precedence over the values of such other object(s) when the value of this object is 'false'; in contrast, when the value of this object is 'true', the values of such other objects take precedence over the value of this object. if 'true', port-queueing mode is enabled. In port-queueing mode, marking and policing is disabled. All queueing on receiving and transmitting is based on QoS tag in the incoming packet. For 802.1Q or ISL-encapsulated packets, queueing is based on the CoS value. Otherwise, queueing is based on the default interface CoS value denoted by csqIfDefaultCos object. if 'false', port-queueing mode is disabled.

csqMarkingStatisticsEnable.name: csqMarkingStatisticsEnable
csqMarkingStatisticsEnable.description: This object specifies whether statistics collection for policy that sets a trust state is enabled at a device-level of granularity, i.e., 'true' = enabled and 'false' = disabled. If no other objects specify whether statistics collection for policy that sets a trust state is enabled at any different level of granularity, then this object's value is not subject to any modifiers. However, some devices might support other object(s) which specify whether statistics collection for policy that sets a trust state is enabled at different level(s) of granularity. For such devices, the value of this object takes precedence over the values of such other object(s) when the value of this object is 'false'; in contrast, when the value of this object is 'true', the values of such other objects take precedence over the value of this object. if 'true', statistics collection is enabled. if 'false', statistics collection is disabled.

csqTenGOnlyMode.name: csqTenGOnlyMode
csqTenGOnlyMode.description: This object specifies whether only 10-Gigabit Ethernet uplink interfaces are used exclusively. 'true' indicates that only the 10-Gigabit Ethernet uplink interfaces are used. The other uplink interfaces which are not of 10-Gigabit capacity will be in administratively down state. 'false' indicates otherwise.

csqServicePoolCellSize.name: csqServicePoolCellSize
csqServicePoolCellSize.description: This object indicates the number of bytes for a service pool cell.

csqCosToDscpTable.name: csqCosToDscpTable
csqCosToDscpTable.description: This table contains the mapping of CoS values to DSCP values. This mapping table consist of eight CoS values (0 through 7) and their corresponding DSCP values. The mapping given by this table is used for all packets received on an interface if and only if that interface has a trust state, as given by the value of csqIfTrustState for the interface, of 'trustCoS'.

csqCosToDscpEntry.name: csqCosToDscpEntry
csqCosToDscpEntry.description: Each row contains the mapping from a CoS value to a DSCP value.

csqCosToDscpCos.name: csqCosToDscpCos
csqCosToDscpCos.description: The CoS value being mapped to the DSCP value.

csqCosToDscpDscp.name: csqCosToDscpDscp
csqCosToDscpDscp.description: The DSCP value which the CoS value maps to.

csqIpPrecToDscpTable.name: csqIpPrecToDscpTable
csqIpPrecToDscpTable.description: This table contains the mapping of IP Precedence to DSCP. This mapping table consist of eight IpPrecedence values (0 through 7) and their corresponding DSCP values. The mapping given by this table is used for all packets received on an interface if and only if that interface has a trust state, as given by the value of csqIfTrustState for the interface, of 'trustIpPrec'.

csqIpPrecToDscpEntry.name: csqIpPrecToDscpEntry
csqIpPrecToDscpEntry.description: Each row contains the mapping from an IP Precedence value to a DSCP value.

csqIpPrecToDscpIpPrec.name: csqIpPrecToDscpIpPrec
csqIpPrecToDscpIpPrec.description: The IP Precedence value being mapped to the DSCP value.

csqIpPrecToDscpDscp.name: csqIpPrecToDscpDscp
csqIpPrecToDscpDscp.description: The DSCP value which the IP Precedence value maps to.

csqExpToDscpTable.name: csqExpToDscpTable
csqExpToDscpTable.description: This table contains the mapping of MPLS-EXP values to DSCP values. This mapping table consist of eight MPLS-EXP values (0 through 7) and their corresponding DSCP values.

csqExpToDscpEntry.name: csqExpToDscpEntry
csqExpToDscpEntry.description: Each row contains the mapping from a EXP value to a DSCP value.

csqExpToDscpExp.name: csqExpToDscpExp
csqExpToDscpExp.description: The EXP value being mapped to the DSCP value.

csqExpToDscpDscp.name: csqExpToDscpDscp
csqExpToDscpDscp.description: The DSCP value which the EXP value maps to.

csqDscpMappingTable.name: csqDscpMappingTable
csqDscpMappingTable.description: This table always has 64 entries, one for each DSCP value. The table contains four mappings from the DSCP value assigned to a packet. One mapping is to the egress CoS to be stored in the layer-2 frame headers for output on 802.1Q or ISL interfaces. Another mapping is to the EXP value to be stored in MPLS label. The other two mappings are to the remarked (or 'marked down') DSCP values which are used when a policer requires that a packet's DSCP value to be modified. Of these two mappings, one is for a normal burst, and the other is for maximum burst.

csqDscpMappingEntry.name: csqDscpMappingEntry
csqDscpMappingEntry.description: Each row contains the mapping from DSCP value to CoS value, MPLS-EXP value and policed DSCP.

csqDscpMappingDscp.name: csqDscpMappingDscp
csqDscpMappingDscp.description: The DSCP value being mapped to the CoS, EXP and policed DSCP value.

csqDscpMappingCos.name: csqDscpMappingCos
csqDscpMappingCos.description: The CoS value which the DSCP values maps to.

csqDscpMappingExp.name: csqDscpMappingExp
csqDscpMappingExp.description: The MPLS-EXP value which the DSCP values maps to.

csqDscpMappingNormalBurstDscp.name: csqDscpMappingNormalBurstDscp
csqDscpMappingNormalBurstDscp.description: The normal burst policed DSCP value which the DSCP values maps to.

csqDscpMappingMaxBurstDscp.name: csqDscpMappingMaxBurstDscp
csqDscpMappingMaxBurstDscp.description: The maximum burst policed DSCP value which the DSCP values maps to.

csqMaxCosMutationMap.name: csqMaxCosMutationMap
csqMaxCosMutationMap.description: The maximum number of CoS mutation map that can be supported in the device.

csqCosMutationTable.name: csqCosMutationTable
csqCosMutationTable.description: This table indicates CoS mutation maps in the device.

csqCosMutationEntry.name: csqCosMutationEntry
csqCosMutationEntry.description: Each row contains the status of this instance. A row instance can be created or removed by setting the appropriate value of its RowStatus object. Once the number of entries in this table reaches the maximum number of CoS mutation map supported in the device denoted by csqMaxCosMutationMap object, user must delete an existing entry in this table in order to create a new entry.

csqCosMutationMapName.name: csqCosMutationMapName
csqCosMutationMapName.description: The name of the CoS mutation map.

csqCosMutationRowStatus.name: csqCosMutationRowStatus
csqCosMutationRowStatus.description: This object is used to manage the creation and deletion of rows in this table.

csqCosMutationMappingTable.name: csqCosMutationMappingTable
csqCosMutationMappingTable.description: This table provides management information for CoS mutation mapping. CoS mutation is applied to ingress traffic. This mutation occurs before the CoS to DSCP mapping for applicable traffic as specified in csqCosToDscpTable.

csqCosMutationMappingEntry.name: csqCosMutationMappingEntry
csqCosMutationMappingEntry.description: Each row contains the mapping from a CoS value to another CoS value. When the entry for csqCosMutationMapName in the csqCosMutationTable is created, corresponding entries in this table are initialized with a default mapping which is the identity function. When the entry for csqCosMutationMapName in the csqCosMutationTable is removed, corresponding entries in this table will also be deleted.

csqCosMutationFromCos.name: csqCosMutationFromCos
csqCosMutationFromCos.description: The input CoS value being mapped to the output CoS value in this mutation map.

csqCosMutationToCos.name: csqCosMutationToCos
csqCosMutationToCos.description: The output CoS value which the input CoS value maps to.

csqMaxDscpMutationMap.name: csqMaxDscpMutationMap
csqMaxDscpMutationMap.description: The maximum number of DSCP mutation map that can be supported in the device.

csqDscpMutationTable.name: csqDscpMutationTable
csqDscpMutationTable.description: This table indicates DSCP mutation maps in the device.

csqDscpMutationEntry.name: csqDscpMutationEntry
csqDscpMutationEntry.description: Each row contains the status of this instance. A row instance can be created or removed by setting the appropriate value of its RowStatus object. Once the number of entries in this table reaches the maximum number of DSCP mutation map supported in the device denoted by csqMaxDscpMutationMap object, user must delete an existing entry in this table in order to create a new entry.

csqDscpMutationMapName.name: csqDscpMutationMapName
csqDscpMutationMapName.description: The name of the DSCP mutation map.

csqDscpMutationRowStatus.name: csqDscpMutationRowStatus
csqDscpMutationRowStatus.description: This object is used to manage the creation and deletion of rows in this table.

csqDscpMutationMappingTable.name: csqDscpMutationMappingTable
csqDscpMutationMappingTable.description: This table provides management information for DSCP mutation mapping. DSCP mutation is applied to egress traffic. This mutation occurs after the mappings specified in csqDscpMappingTable.

csqDscpMutationMappingEntry.name: csqDscpMutationMappingEntry

When the entry for csqDscpMutationMapName in the csqDscpMutationTable is created, corresponding entries in this table are initialized with a default mapping which is the identity function. When the entry for csqDscpMutationMapName in the csqDscpMutationTable is removed, corresponding entries in this table will also be deleted.

csqDscpMutationFromDscp.name: csqDscpMutationFromDscp
csqDscpMutationFromDscp.description: The input DSCP value being mapped to the output DSCP value in this mutation map.

csqDscpMutationToDscp.name: csqDscpMutationToDscp
csqDscpMutationToDscp.description: The output DSCP value which the input DSCP value maps to.

csqMaxExpMutationMap.name: csqMaxExpMutationMap
csqMaxExpMutationMap.description: The maximum number of EXP mutation can be supported in the device.

csqExpMutationTable.name: csqExpMutationTable
csqExpMutationTable.description: This table indicates EXP mutation maps in the device.

csqExpMutationEntry.name: csqExpMutationEntry
csqExpMutationEntry.description: Each row contains the status of this instance. A row instance can be created or removed by setting the appropriate value of its RowStatus object. Once the number of entries in this table reaches the maximum number of EXP mutation map supported in the device denoted by csqMaxExpMutationMap object, user must delete an existing entry in this table in order to create a new entry.

csqExpMutationMapName.name: csqExpMutationMapName
csqExpMutationMapName.description: The name of the EXP mutation map.

csqExpMutationRowStatus.name: csqExpMutationRowStatus
csqExpMutationRowStatus.description: This object is used to manage the creation and deletion of rows in this table.

csqExpMutationMappingTable.name: csqExpMutationMappingTable
csqExpMutationMappingTable.description: This table provides management information for EXP mutation mapping. EXP mutation is applied to egress traffic. This mutation occurs after the mapping specified in csqExpToDscpTable.

csqExpMutationMappingEntry.name: csqExpMutationMappingEntry
csqExpMutationMappingEntry.description: Each row contains the mapping from input EXP to output EXP value. When the entry for csqExpMutationMapName in the csqExpMutationTable is created, corresponding entries in this table are initialized with a default mapping which is the identity function. When the entry for csqExpMutationMapName in the csqExpMutationTable is removed, corresponding entries in this table will also be deleted.

csqExpMutationFromExp.name: csqExpMutationFromExp
csqExpMutationFromExp.description: The input EXP value being mapped to the output EXP value in this mutation map.

csqExpMutationToExp.name: csqExpMutationToExp
csqExpMutationToExp.description: The output EXP value which the input EXP value maps to.

csqIfMutationConfigTable.name: csqIfMutationConfigTable
csqIfMutationConfigTable.description: A table containing the mutation configuration for mutation capable interface in the device. If a mutation capable interface does not have a row in this table, there is no mutation performed at such interface.

csqIfMutationConfigEntry.name: csqIfMutationConfigEntry
csqIfMutationConfigEntry.description: A row instance contains the name of CoS, DSCP and EXP mutation map and RowStatus object.

csqIfCosMutationMap.name: csqIfCosMutationMap
csqIfCosMutationMap.description: This object specifies the name of CoS mutation map applied at this interface. If CoS mutation is not performed at the interface, then the value of this object is the zero-length string; otherwise, the value of this object must be the name of a row in the csqCosMutationTable. If a row in the csqCosMutationTable is deleted, all instances of this object which referenced the deleted row get changed to the zero-length string.

csqIfDscpMutationMap.name: csqIfDscpMutationMap
csqIfDscpMutationMap.description: This object specifies the name of DSCP mutation map applied at this interface. If DSCP mutation is not performed at the interface, then the value of this object is the zero-length string; otherwise, the value of this object must be the name of a row in the csqDscpMutationTable. If a row in the csqDscpMutationTable is deleted, all instances of this object which referenced the deleted row get changed to the zero-length string.

csqIfExpMutationMap.name: csqIfExpMutationMap
csqIfExpMutationMap.description: This object specifies the name of EXP mutation map applied at this interface. If EXP mutation is not performed at the interface, then the value of this object is the zero-length string; otherwise, the value of this object must be the name of a row in the csqExpMutationTable. If a row in the csqExpMutationTable is deleted, all instances of this object which referenced the deleted row get changed to the zero-length string.

csqIfMutationRowStatus.name: csqIfMutationRowStatus
csqIfMutationRowStatus.description: This object is used to manage the creation, and deletion of rows in the table.

csqIfConfigTable.name: csqIfConfigTable
csqIfConfigTable.description: This table provides QoS configuration for QoS manageable interface in the device.

csqIfConfigEntry.name: csqIfConfigEntry
csqIfConfigEntry.description: A row instance contains the default CoS value and trust state of a Qos manageable interface.

csqIfDefaultCos.name: csqIfDefaultCos
csqIfDefaultCos.description: This object specifies the default CoS value configured at this physical interface. This default value will be assigned to packet which does not have a CoS value in its layer-2 header when the packet arrives at this interface or if the value of csqIfTrustState object for this physical interface is 'untrusted'.

csqIfTrustState.name: csqIfTrustState
csqIfTrustState.description: This object is used to set the trust state of an interface. (whether the packets arriving at an interface are trusted to carry the correct data for classification.) If the object is untrusted(1), then the DSCP assigned to the packet is the layer2 CoS value denoted by csqIfDefaultCos object mapped to a DSCP by the CoS-to-DSCP mapping defined in object csqCosToDscpDscp. If this object is trustCoS(2), then the DSCP assigned to the packet is the layer2 CoS of the packet mapped to a DSCP by the CoS-to-DSCP mapping defined in object csqCosToDscpDscp. When this object is trustIpPrec(3), a DSCP is assigned to an IP packet according to the IP-Precedence-to-DSCP mapping defined by the values contained in csqIpPrecToDscpTable. For non-IP packets, trustIpPrec(3) has identical behavior as trustCoS(2). When this object is trustDscp(4), the DSCP contained in an IP packet is trusted as being the correct value to assign to it. For non-IP packets, trustDscp(4) has identical behavior as trustCoS(2).

csqIfQueueModeCpb.name: csqIfQueueModeCpb
csqIfQueueModeCpb.description: This object indicates the queue mode capability at this interface. 'cos' indicates that the interface is capable of queueing a packet based on the CoS value of the packet. 'dscp' indicates that the interface is capable of queueing a packet based on the DSCP value of the packet.

csqIfConfigQueueMode.name: csqIfConfigQueueMode
csqIfConfigQueueMode.description: Specifies the queueing mode at this interface. 'cos' indicates that the interface is queueing a packet based on the CoS value of the packet. This value can only be set if the 'cos' bit of csqIfQueueModeCpb is set. 'dscp' indicates that the interface is queueing a packet based on the DSCP value of the packet. This value can only be set if the 'dscp' bit of csqIfQueueModeCpb is set.

csqIfIngressPolicyMap.name: csqIfIngressPolicyMap
csqIfIngressPolicyMap.description: Specifies the name of an existing policy-map attached to this interface in ingress direction. If there is no such policy-map attached, the value of this object is zero-length string.

csqIfEgressPolicyMap.name: csqIfEgressPolicyMap
csqIfEgressPolicyMap.description: Specifies the name of an existing policy-map attached to this interface in egress direction. If there is no such policy-map attached, the value of this object is zero-length string.

csqIfIngressQueueingEnable.name: csqIfIngressQueueingEnable
csqIfIngressQueueingEnable.description: This object indicates if ingress queueing is enabled at this interface. 'true' indicates ingress queueing is enabled. 'false' indicates ingress queueing is disabled.

csqIfEgressQueueingEnable.name: csqIfEgressQueueingEnable
csqIfEgressQueueingEnable.description: This object indicates if egress queueing is enabled at this interface. 'true' indicates egress queueing is enabled. 'false' indicates egress queueing is disabled.

csqIfQueueingTrustState.name: csqIfQueueingTrustState
csqIfQueueingTrustState.description: This object indicates the queueing trust state of an interface. If the object is untrusted(1), then the DSCP assigned to the packet is the layer2 CoS value denoted by csqIfDefaultCos object mapped to a DSCP by the CoS-to-DSCP mapping defined in object csqCosToDscpDscp. If this object is trustCoS(2), then the DSCP assigned to the packet is the layer2 CoS of the packet mapped to a DSCP by the CoS-to-DSCP mapping defined in object csqCosToDscpDscp. When this object is trustIpPrec(3), a DSCP is assigned to an IP packet according to the IP-Precedence-to-DSCP mapping defined by the values contained in csqIpPrecToDscpTable. For non-IP packets, trustIpPrec(3) has identical behavior as trustCoS(2). When this object is trustDscp(4), the DSCP contained in an IP packet is trusted as being the correct value to assign to it. For non-IP packets, trustDscp(4) has identical behavior as trustCoS(2).

csqIfCosToQueueTable.name: csqIfCosToQueueTable
csqIfCosToQueueTable.description: This table provides the information for and configuration of assigning packets to queues and thresholds based on their CoS value.

csqIfCosToQueueEntry.name: csqIfCosToQueueEntry
csqIfCosToQueueEntry.description: The assignment of packets at an interface to a pair of queue and threshold based on their CoS value and traffic direction.

csqIfCosToQueueDirection.name: csqIfCosToQueueDirection
csqIfCosToQueueDirection.description: The traffic direction of a packet.

csqIfCosToQueueCos.name: csqIfCosToQueueCos
csqIfCosToQueueCos.description: The CoS value of the packet which the queue and threshold assignment is based on.

csqIfCosToQueueQueueNumber.name: csqIfCosToQueueQueueNumber
csqIfCosToQueueQueueNumber.description: The queue number where packet whose CoS value denoted by csqIfCosToQueueCos will be assigned to.

csqIfCosToQueueThresholdNumber.name: csqIfCosToQueueThresholdNumber
csqIfCosToQueueThresholdNumber.description: The threshold number where packet whose CoS value denoted by csqIfCosToQueueCos will be assigned to.

csqIfDscpToQueueTable.name: csqIfDscpToQueueTable
csqIfDscpToQueueTable.description: This table provides the information for and configuration of assigning packets to queues and thresholds based on their DSCP value and traffic direction.

csqIfDscpToQueueEntry.name: csqIfDscpToQueueEntry
csqIfDscpToQueueEntry.description: The assignment of packets at an interface to a pair of queue and threshold based on their DSCP value and packets traffic direction.

csqIfDscpToQueueDirection.name: csqIfDscpToQueueDirection
csqIfDscpToQueueDirection.description: The traffic direction of a packet.

csqIfDscpToQueueDscp.name: csqIfDscpToQueueDscp
csqIfDscpToQueueDscp.description: The DSCP value of the packet which the queue and threshold assignment is based on.

csqIfDscpToQueueQueueNumber.name: csqIfDscpToQueueQueueNumber
csqIfDscpToQueueQueueNumber.description: The queue number where packet whose DSCP value denoted by csqIfDscpToQueueDscp will be assigned to.

csqIfDscpToQueueThresholdNumber.name: csqIfDscpToQueueThresholdNumber
csqIfDscpToQueueThresholdNumber.description: The threshold number where packet whose DSCP value denoted by csqIfDscpToQueueDscp will be assigned to.

csqIfDropConfigTable.name: csqIfDropConfigTable
csqIfDropConfigTable.description: This table maintains threshold parameters for the specified queue number and threshold number of an interface.

csqIfDropConfigEntry.name: csqIfDropConfigEntry
csqIfDropConfigEntry.description: For each threshold of a queue, there are parameters to set on the threshold. This entry contains the parameters.

csqIfDropConfigDropAlgorithm.name: csqIfDropConfigDropAlgorithm
csqIfDropConfigDropAlgorithm.description: Specifies the drop algorithm running at this queue and threshold. 'tailDrop' indicates that this queue and threshold drops packet using tail-drop algorithm. This value is configurable only if 'tailDrop' bit in the value of qosIfCapabilities object for the same ifIndex and traffic direction is set. 'wred' indicates that WRED algorithm is used. This value is configurable only if 'wred' bit in the value of qosIfCapabilities object for the same ifIndex and traffic direction is set.

csqIfDropConfigDropThreshold.name: csqIfDropConfigDropThreshold
csqIfDropConfigDropThreshold.description: This object specifies the drop threshold parameter for a pair of queue and threshold of an interface when the drop algorithm is tail drop. Once the packets in the buffer is more than the value of this object, the incoming packets of the buffer are dropped. The value is a percentage of the full buffer. This object is configurable only if 'tailDrop' bit in the value of qosIfCapabilities for the same ifIndex and traffic direction is set. If value of csqIfDropConfigAlgorithm is not 'tailDrop', this object value has no effect. If value of csqIfDropConfigQueueBuffer is not 'percent', this object value has no effect.

csqIfDropConfigMinWredThreshold.name: csqIfDropConfigMinWredThreshold
csqIfDropConfigMinWredThreshold.description: This object specifies the min WRED threshold parameter of a threshold number for the specific interface when WRED drop algorithm is used. WRED (Weighted Random Early Detect) is a mechanism which drops packets fairly during congestion so that adaptive applications can react to congestion. This object specifies a percentage of the buffer size. This object is configurable only if 'wred' bit in the value of qosIfCapabilities object for the same ifIndex and traffic direction is set. If value of csqIfDropConfigAlgorithm is not 'wred', this object value has no effect.

csqIfDropConfigMaxWredThreshold.name: csqIfDropConfigMaxWredThreshold
csqIfDropConfigMaxWredThreshold.description: This object specifies the max WRED threshold parameter of a threshold number for the specific interface when WRED drop algorithm is used. This object is configurable only if 'wred' bit in the value of qosIfCapabilities object for the same ifIndex and traffic direction is set. If value of csqIfDropConfigAlgorithm is not 'wred', this object value has no effect.

csqIfDropConfigQueueBuffer.name: csqIfDropConfigQueueBuffer
csqIfDropConfigQueueBuffer.description: This object specifies how the queue buffer behaves when the drop algorithm is tail drop. 'shared' indicates that the queue buffer is shared among all queues at the interface. 'dedicated' indicates that each queue will be assigned a dedicated portion of the queue buffer. 'percent' indicates that a percentage of the queue buffer can be configured for each queue. The percentage value can be configured via csqIfDropConfigDropThreshold object. This object is configurable only if 'tailDrop' bit in the value of qosIfCapabilities for the same ifIndex and traffic direction is set. If value of csqIfDropConfigAlgorithm is not 'tailDrop', this object value has no effect.

csqIfQueueTable.name: csqIfQueueTable
csqIfQueueTable.description: A table containing configuration parameter for each queue on a QOS managable interface.

csqIfQueueEntry.name: csqIfQueueEntry
csqIfQueueEntry.description: A set of WRR weight and queue size allocation weight for ingress or egress of a specific queue.

csqIfQueueWrrWeight.name: csqIfQueueWrrWeight
csqIfQueueWrrWeight.description: Specifies the WRR weight. This object is configurable only if the value of csqIfQueueScheduling is 'wrr'. When the value of csqIfQueueScheduling is not 'wrr', the value of this object has no effect.

csqIfQueueStatsGranularity.name: csqIfQueueStatsGranularity
csqIfQueueStatsGranularity.description: Indicates whether QoS statistics is maintained per queue or per queue per threshold. 'perQueue' indicates that QoS statistics is maintained per queue. 'perQueueThresh' indicates that QoS statistics is maintained per queue per threshold.

csqIfQueueClassMapName.name: csqIfQueueClassMapName
csqIfQueueClassMapName.description: Specifies the name of an existing class-map attached at this interface for a queue in the specified direction. If there is no such class-map attached, the value of this object is zero-length string.

csqIfQueueScheduling.name: csqIfQueueScheduling
csqIfQueueScheduling.description: Specifies the queue scheduling method. 'wrr' indicates that the queue scheduling method is Weight Round Robin. 'srr' indicates that the queue scheduling method is Shaped Round Robin.

csqIfQueueSrrWeight.name: csqIfQueueSrrWeight
csqIfQueueSrrWeight.description: Specifies the SRR weight. This object is configurable only if the value of csqIfQueueScheduling is 'srr'. When the value of csqIfQueueScheduling is not 'srr', the value of this object has no effect.

csqIfModeConfigTable.name: csqIfModeConfigTable
csqIfModeConfigTable.description: A table used to configure the QoS mode for layer-2 interface.

csqIfModeConfigEntry.name: csqIfModeConfigEntry
csqIfModeConfigEntry.description: An entry containing QoS mode information of layer-2 interface.

csqIfVlanBasedQosModeEnable.name: csqIfVlanBasedQosModeEnable
csqIfVlanBasedQosModeEnable.description: Specifies if VLAN-based mode is enabled or disabled at the specified interface. If 'true', policy map that is attached to this interface has no effect, and QoS is driven by the policy map that is attached to the corresponding VLAN interface that this interface belongs to. Otherwise, the value of this object is 'false'.

csqIfConsistencyCheckTable.name: csqIfConsistencyCheckTable
csqIfConsistencyCheckTable.description: A table used to configure the QoS-port attribute consistency check for Port Channel interface identified by ifIndex. QoS-port attribute consistency check consists of but not limited to checking for members of a Port Channel interface having the same queue type.

csqIfConsistencyCheckEntry.name: csqIfConsistencyCheckEntry
csqIfConsistencyCheckEntry.description: An entry containing QoS-port attribute consistency check information of Port Channel interface.

csqIfConsistencyCheckEnable.name: csqIfConsistencyCheckEnable
csqIfConsistencyCheckEnable.description: Specifies if QoS-port attribute consitency check is enabled or disabled at the specified channel interface. If 'true', QoS-port attribute consistency check is enabled. If 'false', QoS-port attribute consistency check is disabled.

csqIfQosGroupInfoTable.name: csqIfQosGroupInfoTable
csqIfQosGroupInfoTable.description: This table provides QoS group information for QoS manageable interfaces in the device.

csqIfQosGroupInfoEntry.name: csqIfQosGroupInfoEntry
csqIfQosGroupInfoEntry.description: A row instance contains Qos group information, which are per interface (ifIndex), per traffic direction, per QoS group.

csqIfQosGroupInfoGroupNumber.name: csqIfQosGroupInfoGroupNumber
csqIfQosGroupInfoGroupNumber.description: This object indicates a specific QoS group.

csqIfQosGroupInfoQueueSize.name: csqIfQosGroupInfoQueueSize
csqIfQosGroupInfoQueueSize.description: This object indicates the ingress queue size. Value 0 indicates it's not applicable for this direction.

csqIfQosGroupInfoHwMTU.name: csqIfQosGroupInfoHwMTU
csqIfQosGroupInfoHwMTU.description: This object indicates the hardware MTU. Value 0 indicates it's not applicable for this direction.

csqIfQosGroupInfoMTU.name: csqIfQosGroupInfoMTU
csqIfQosGroupInfoMTU.description: This object indicates the MTU applied via QoS policy. Value 0 indicates it's not applicable for this direction.

csqIfQosGroupInfoDropType.name: csqIfQosGroupInfoDropType
csqIfQosGroupInfoDropType.description: This object indicates the drop type.

csqIfQosGroupInfoResumeThresh.name: csqIfQosGroupInfoResumeThresh
csqIfQosGroupInfoResumeThresh.description: This object indicates the buffer limit (In Bytes) at which the port resumes the peer. Value 0 indicates it's not applicable for this direction.

csqIfQosGroupInfoPauseThresh.name: csqIfQosGroupInfoPauseThresh
csqIfQosGroupInfoPauseThresh.description: This object indicates the buffer limit (In Bytes) at which the port pauses the peer. Value 0 indicates it's not applicable for this direction.

csqIfQosGroupInfoScheduling.name: csqIfQosGroupInfoScheduling
csqIfQosGroupInfoScheduling.description: This object indicates the scheduling type applied via QoS policy.

csqIfQosGroupInfoBandwidth.name: csqIfQosGroupInfoBandwidth
csqIfQosGroupInfoBandwidth.description: This object indicates the bandwidth. Value 0 indicates it's not applicable for this direction.

csqIfQosGroupInfoBandwidthUnits.name: csqIfQosGroupInfoBandwidthUnits
csqIfQosGroupInfoBandwidthUnits.description: This object indicates the unit of csqIfQosGroupInfoBandwidth.

csqIfQosGroupInfoShapeMinThresh.name: csqIfQosGroupInfoShapeMinThresh
csqIfQosGroupInfoShapeMinThresh.description: This object indicates the shape minimum threshold. Value 0 indicates it's not applicable for this direction.

csqIfQosGroupInfoShapeMaxThresh.name: csqIfQosGroupInfoShapeMaxThresh
csqIfQosGroupInfoShapeMaxThresh.description: This object indicates the shape maximum threshold. Value 0 indicates it's not applicable for this direction.

csqIfQosGroupInfoShapeUnits.name: csqIfQosGroupInfoShapeUnits
csqIfQosGroupInfoShapeUnits.description: This object indicates the unit of csqIfQosGroupInfoShapeMinThresh and csqIfQosGroupInfoShapeMaxThresh.

csqIfStatsTable.name: csqIfStatsTable
csqIfStatsTable.description: A table containing QoS statistics counters per QoS manageable interface.

csqIfStatsEntry.name: csqIfStatsEntry
csqIfStatsEntry.description: An entry contains statistics, such as a drop packet counter, which are per interface (ifIndex), per direction, per queue and per threshold.

csqIfStatsDirection.name: csqIfStatsDirection
csqIfStatsDirection.description: Indicates traffic direction of an interface.

csqIfStatsQueueNumber.name: csqIfStatsQueueNumber
csqIfStatsQueueNumber.description: Indicates the queue number of the interface for which statistics are collected. For example : if the interface has a queue type of oneP2Q2t, this index value can be 1, 2, 3.

csqIfStatsThresholdNumber.name: csqIfStatsThresholdNumber
csqIfStatsThresholdNumber.description: Indicates the threshold number of a queue on the interface for which statistics are collected. For example : if the interface has a queue type of oneP2Q2t, this index value can be 1, 2. If the value of the corresponding csqIfQueueStatsGranularity for the queue that this csqIfStatsThresholdNumber belongs to is 'perQueue', this csqIfStatsThresholdNumber index value is always 1.

csqIfStatsDropPkts.name: csqIfStatsDropPkts
csqIfStatsDropPkts.description: The number of packets that have been received then dropped from the interface because they exceeded the threshold value configured at this queue and threshold of this interface.

csqModuleStatsTable.name: csqModuleStatsTable
csqModuleStatsTable.description: A table decribes QoS statistics counters per module that is capable of providing this information. Such module is identified by the entPhysicalIndex in ENTITY-MIB.

csqModuleStatsEntry.name: csqModuleStatsEntry
csqModuleStatsEntry.description: An entry contains per-module (entPhysicalIndex) statistics such as the number of dropped packets due to policing, number of IP packets with their ToS and CoS value changed, number of non IP packets with their CoS value changed, and number of MPLS packets with their EXP value changed.

csqModuleDropByPolicingPackets.name: csqModuleDropByPolicingPackets
csqModuleDropByPolicingPackets.description: The number of packets that have been dropped due to policing.

csqModuleTosChangedIpPackets.name: csqModuleTosChangedIpPackets
csqModuleTosChangedIpPackets.description: The number of IP packets that have the ToS value changed due to policing.

csqModuleCosChangedIpPackets.name: csqModuleCosChangedIpPackets
csqModuleCosChangedIpPackets.description: The number of IP packets that have the CoS value changed due to policing.

csqModuleCosChangedNonIpPackets.name: csqModuleCosChangedNonIpPackets
csqModuleCosChangedNonIpPackets.description: The number of non IP packets that have the CoS value changed due to policing.

csqModuleExpChangedMplsPackets.name: csqModuleExpChangedMplsPackets
csqModuleExpChangedMplsPackets.description: The number of MPLS packets have the EXP value change due to policing.

csqModuleStatsExtTable.name: csqModuleStatsExtTable
csqModuleStatsExtTable.description: This table describes additional QoS statistics counters per module that is capable of providing this information. Such module is identified by the entPhysicalIndex in ENTITY-MIB.

csqModuleStatsExtEntry.name: csqModuleStatsExtEntry
csqModuleStatsExtEntry.description: Each entry contains additional per-module (entPhysicalIndex) QoS statistics.

csqModuleTunnelEncapPackets.name: csqModuleTunnelEncapPackets
csqModuleTunnelEncapPackets.description: The total number of tunnel encapsulated packets.

csqModuleTunnelDecapPackets.name: csqModuleTunnelDecapPackets
csqModuleTunnelDecapPackets.description: The total number of tunnel decapsulated packets.

csqModuleDropByPolicingInOctets.description: The total number of ingress octets which are dropped due to policing.

csqModuleDropByPolicingOutOctets.name: csqModuleDropByPolicingOutOctets
csqModuleDropByPolicingOutOctets.description: The total number of egress octets which are dropped due to policing.

csqModuleFwdByPolicingInPackets.description: The total number of policed ingress packets which are forwarded.

csqModuleFwdByPolicingInOctets.name: csqModuleFwdByPolicingInOctets
csqModuleFwdByPolicingInOctets.description: The total number of policed ingress octets which are forwarded.

csqModuleFwdByPolicingOutPackets.name: csqModuleFwdByPolicingOutPackets
csqModuleFwdByPolicingOutPackets.description: The total number of policed egress packets which are forwarded.

csqModuleFwdByPolicingOutOctets.name: csqModuleFwdByPolicingOutOctets
csqModuleFwdByPolicingOutOctets.description: The total number of policed egress octets which are forwarded.

csqModuleHighExceedInPackets.name: csqModuleHighExceedInPackets
csqModuleHighExceedInPackets.description: The total number of ingress packets exceeding the high level policing rate.

csqModuleHighExceedInOctets.name: csqModuleHighExceedInOctets

csqModuleHighExceedOutPackets.name: csqModuleHighExceedOutPackets

csqModuleHighExceedOutOctets.name: csqModuleHighExceedOutOctets

csqModuleLowExceedInPackets.name: csqModuleLowExceedInPackets

csqModuleLowExceedInOctets.name: csqModuleLowExceedInOctets

csqModuleLowExceedOutPackets.name: csqModuleLowExceedOutPackets
csqModuleLowExceedOutPackets.description: The total number of egress packets exceeding the low level policing rate.

csqModuleLowExceedOutOctets.name: csqModuleLowExceedOutOctets
csqModuleLowExceedOutOctets.description: The total number of egress octets exceeding the low level policing rate.

csqModuleDropByAggPolicerInPackets.name: csqModuleDropByAggPolicerInPackets
csqModuleDropByAggPolicerInPackets.description: The total number of ingress packets which are dropped by aggregate policers.

csqModuleDropByAggPolicerInOctets.name: csqModuleDropByAggPolicerInOctets
csqModuleDropByAggPolicerInOctets.description: The total number of ingress octets which are dropped by aggregate policer.

csqModuleDropByAggPolicerOutPackets.name: csqModuleDropByAggPolicerOutPackets
csqModuleDropByAggPolicerOutPackets.description: The total number of egress packets which are dropped by aggregate policers.

csqModuleDropByAggPolicerOutOctets.name: csqModuleDropByAggPolicerOutOctets
csqModuleDropByAggPolicerOutOctets.description: The total number of egress octets which are dropped by aggregate policers.

csqModuleFwdByAggPolicerInPackets.name: csqModuleFwdByAggPolicerInPackets
csqModuleFwdByAggPolicerInPackets.description: The total number of ingress packets which are forwarded by aggregate policers.

csqModuleFwdByAggPolicerInOctets.name: csqModuleFwdByAggPolicerInOctets
csqModuleFwdByAggPolicerInOctets.description: The total number of ingress octets which are forwarded by aggregate policers.

csqModuleFwdByAggPolicerOutPackets.name: csqModuleFwdByAggPolicerOutPackets
csqModuleFwdByAggPolicerOutPackets.description: The total number of egress packets which are forwarded by aggregate policers.

csqModuleFwdByAggPolicerOutOctets.name: csqModuleFwdByAggPolicerOutOctets
csqModuleFwdByAggPolicerOutOctets.description: The total number of egress octets which are forwarded by aggregate policers.

csqModuleAggHighExceedInPackets.name: csqModuleAggHighExceedInPackets
csqModuleAggHighExceedInPackets.description: The total number of ingress packets (policed by aggregate policers) exceeding the high level policing rate.

csqModuleAggHighExceedInOctets.name: csqModuleAggHighExceedInOctets
csqModuleAggHighExceedInOctets.description: The total number of ingress octets (policed by aggregate policers) exceeding the high level policing rate.

csqModuleAggHighExceedOutPackets.name: csqModuleAggHighExceedOutPackets
csqModuleAggHighExceedOutPackets.description: The total number of egress packets (policed by aggregate policers) exceeding the high level policing rate.

csqModuleAggHighExceedOutOctets.name: csqModuleAggHighExceedOutOctets
csqModuleAggHighExceedOutOctets.description: The total number of egress octets (policed by aggregate policers) exceeding the high level policing rate.

csqModuleAggLowExceedInPackets.name: csqModuleAggLowExceedInPackets
csqModuleAggLowExceedInPackets.description: The total number of ingress packets (policed by aggregate policers) exceeding the low level policing rate.

csqModuleAggLowExceedInOctets.name: csqModuleAggLowExceedInOctets

csqModuleAggLowExceedOutOctets.name: csqModuleAggLowExceedOutOctets

csqModuleDropByNetflowInPackets.name: csqModuleDropByNetflowInPackets
csqModuleDropByNetflowInPackets.description: The total number of ingress packets which are dropped by the netflow feature.

csqModuleDropByNetflowInOctets.name: csqModuleDropByNetflowInOctets
csqModuleDropByNetflowInOctets.description: The total number of ingress octets which are dropped by the netflow feature.

csqModuleDropByNetflowOutPackets.name: csqModuleDropByNetflowOutPackets
csqModuleDropByNetflowOutPackets.description: The total number of egress packets which are dropped by the netflow feature.

csqModuleDropByNetflowOutOctets.name: csqModuleDropByNetflowOutOctets
csqModuleDropByNetflowOutOctets.description: The total number of egress octets which are dropped by the netflow feature.

csqModuleFwdByNetflowInPackets.name: csqModuleFwdByNetflowInPackets
csqModuleFwdByNetflowInPackets.description: The total number of ingress packets which are forwarded by the netflow feature.

csqModuleFwdByNetflowInOctets.name: csqModuleFwdByNetflowInOctets
csqModuleFwdByNetflowInOctets.description: The total number of ingress octets which are forwarded by the netflow feature.

csqModuleFwdByNetflowOutPackets.name: csqModuleFwdByNetflowOutPackets
csqModuleFwdByNetflowOutPackets.description: The total number of egress packets which are forwarded by the netflow feature.

csqModuleFwdByNetflowOutOctets.name: csqModuleFwdByNetflowOutOctets
csqModuleFwdByNetflowOutOctets.description: The total number of egress octets which are forwarded by the netflow feature.

csqModuleNetflowExceedInPackets.name: csqModuleNetflowExceedInPackets
csqModuleNetflowExceedInPackets.description: The total number of ingress packets exceeding the netflow policing rate.

csqModuleNetflowExceedInOctets.name: csqModuleNetflowExceedInOctets
csqModuleNetflowExceedInOctets.description: The total number of ingress octets exceeding the netflow policing rate.

csqModuleNetflowExceedOutPackets.name: csqModuleNetflowExceedOutPackets
csqModuleNetflowExceedOutPackets.description: The total number of egress packets exceeding the netflow policing rate.

csqModuleNetflowExceedOutOctets.name: csqModuleNetflowExceedOutOctets
csqModuleNetflowExceedOutOctets.description: The total number of egress octets exceeding the netflow policing rate.

csqModuleCosChangedPackets.name: csqModuleCosChangedPackets
csqModuleCosChangedPackets.description: The number of packets (IP and non-IP) that have the CoS value changed due to policing.

csqModuleTrafficClassChangedPackets.name: csqModuleTrafficClassChangedPackets
csqModuleTrafficClassChangedPackets.description: The number of packets that have the Traffic Class changed due to policing

csqIfStatsExtTable.name: csqIfStatsExtTable
csqIfStatsExtTable.description: A table containing QoS statistics counters per QoS manageable interface.

csqIfStatsExtEntry.name: csqIfStatsExtEntry
csqIfStatsExtEntry.description: Each entry contains statistics, such as a drop BPDU packet counter, which are per interface (ifIndex), per direction.

csqIfBpduDropPkts.name: csqIfBpduDropPkts
csqIfBpduDropPkts.description: The total number of dropped BPDU packets.

csqIfQosGroupStatsTable.name: csqIfQosGroupStatsTable
csqIfQosGroupStatsTable.description: A table containing QoS statistics counters on QoS manageable interfaces.

csqIfQosGroupStatsEntry.name: csqIfQosGroupStatsEntry
csqIfQosGroupStatsEntry.description: An entry contains a specific statistics, which are per interface (ifIndex), per traffic direction, per QoS group.

csqIfQosGroupStatsGroupNumber.name: csqIfQosGroupStatsGroupNumber
csqIfQosGroupStatsGroupNumber.description: This object indicates a specific QoS group on the interface.

csqIfQosGroupStatsType.name: csqIfQosGroupStatsType
csqIfQosGroupStatsType.description: This object indicates a specific statistics counter type.

csqIfQosGroupStatsValue.name: csqIfQosGroupStatsValue
csqIfQosGroupStatsValue.description: This object indicates the value of the specific statistics counter.

csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageTable.name: csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageTable
csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageTable.description: A table contains the utilization of the buffer allocated for a specific priority group on the ingress of the QoS manageable interfaces.

csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageEntry.name: csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageEntry
csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageEntry.description: An entry indicates the per interface per priority group buffer utilization on ingress direction. The unit of the value of each object is cell. A cell represents the number of bytes, which is indicated by scalar object csqServicePoolCellSize.

csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageGrpNo.name: csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageGrpNo
csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageGrpNo.description: This object indicates a specific priority group on the interface.

csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageMinCount.name: csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageMinCount
csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageMinCount.description: This object indicates the current usage of cells used out of the minimum reserved buffer.

csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageSharedCount.name: csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageSharedCount
csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageSharedCount.description: This object indicates the current usage of cells used out of the shared pool.

csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageHeadroomCount.name: csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageHeadroomCount
csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageHeadroomCount.description: This object indicates current usage of cells out of the reserved headroom buffer. Headroom buffer is reserved to account for PFC control frame round trip delays.

csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageGlobalHeadroomCount.name: csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageGlobalHeadroomCount
csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageGlobalHeadroomCount.description: This object indicates current usage of cells out of the global headroom buffer. Global headroom buffer is reserved and shared across all interfaces.

csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageSharedPeekCount.name: csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageSharedPeekCount
csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageSharedPeekCount.description: This object indicates peak usage of cells out of the shared pool.

csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageHeadroomPeekCount.name: csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageHeadroomPeekCount
csqIfPriGrpInBufUsageHeadroomPeekCount.description: This object indicates peak usage of cells out of the reserved headroom buffer.

csqSharedPoolUsageTable.name: csqSharedPoolUsageTable
csqSharedPoolUsageTable.description: A table contains the utilization of the shared service pool in the system.

csqSharedPoolUsageEntry.name: csqSharedPoolUsageEntry
csqSharedPoolUsageEntry.description: An entry indicates the utilization of an shared service pool on a particular physical device, which is identified by a specific module(indicated by entPhysicalIndex in ENTITY-MIB) and instance (indicated by csqSharedPoolUsageInstNo). The unit of the value of the objects is cell. A cell represents the number of bytes, which is indicated by scalar object csqServicePoolCellSize.

csqSharedPoolUsageInstNo.name: csqSharedPoolUsageInstNo
csqSharedPoolUsageInstNo.description: This object indicates an arbitrary number which uniquely identifies the instance number of a specific internal device.

csqSharedPoolUsagePoolNo.name: csqSharedPoolUsagePoolNo
csqSharedPoolUsagePoolNo.description: This object indicates the service pool number.

csqSharedPoolUsageUsed.name: csqSharedPoolUsageUsed
csqSharedPoolUsageUsed.description: This object indicates the number of used cells in a shared pool.

csqSharedPoolUsageRemain.name: csqSharedPoolUsageRemain
csqSharedPoolUsageRemain.description: This object indicates the remaining cells in a shared pool.

csqSharedPoolUsagePeak.name: csqSharedPoolUsagePeak
csqSharedPoolUsagePeak.description: This object indicates the peak used cells in a shared pool.

csqSharedPoolUsageTotal.name: csqSharedPoolUsageTotal
csqSharedPoolUsageTotal.description: This object indicates the total cells in a shared pool.

csqSharedPoolUsageUsedTx.name: csqSharedPoolUsageUsedTx
csqSharedPoolUsageUsedTx.description: This object indicates the number of used cells in a output shared pool.

csqSharedPoolUsageRemainTx.name: csqSharedPoolUsageRemainTx
csqSharedPoolUsageRemainTx.description: This object indicates the remaining cells in a output shared pool.

csqSharedPoolUsagePeakTx.name: csqSharedPoolUsagePeakTx
csqSharedPoolUsagePeakTx.description: This object indicates the peak used cells in a output shared pool.

csqSharedPoolUsageTotalTx.name: csqSharedPoolUsageTotalTx
csqSharedPoolUsageTotalTx.description: This object indicates the total cells in a output shared pool.

csqSharedPoolUsageNameTx.name: csqSharedPoolUsageNameTx
csqSharedPoolUsageNameTx.description: Indicates the name of output shared pool.

csqHwSharedPoolUsageTable.name: csqHwSharedPoolUsageTable
